-- UniCredit's Rampl May Resign After Management Shakeup, Corriere Reports
-- B y   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 2010-10-28T05:33:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/unicredit-s-rampl-may-resign-after-management-shakeup-corriere-reports.html
UniCredit SpA  Chairman  Dieter Rampl 
may resign after the company’s board decided against the
appointment of a second general manager at Italy’s largest bank,
daily Corriere della Sera reported, without saying where it got
the information.  Rampl wanted a second general manager to oversee the
investment banking business, according to the Italian newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Armorel Kenna  in Milan at 
 akenna@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net  